<heading id="D0E5F92D611BFFEEFF23FF0A759BC7B1" bold="true" box="[192,427,198,222]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" reason="4">
<emphasis id="B9669253611BFFEEFF23FF0A759BC7B1" bold="true" box="[192,427,198,222]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
Tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611BFFEEFEF3FF0A759BC7B1" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1855" box="[272,427,198,222]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Liparetrini">Liparetrini</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3081DCA611BFFEEFF23FECA7728C6B1" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BAD4E41611BFFEEFF23FECA7728C6B1" blockId="9.[192,1441,262,478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B9669253611BFFEEFF23FECA7575C671" bold="true" box="[192,325,262,286]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(modified from 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8333B0611BFFEEFE1FFECA76A7C671" author="Britton, E. B." box="[508,663,262,286]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="159 - 195" refId="ref17851" refString="Britton, E. B. 1990. A synopsis of the Australian genera of Liparetrini (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Invertebrate Taxonomy 4: 159 - 195." type="journal article" year="1990">Britton 1990</bibRefCitation>
). Antennae with 8-10 antennomeres, including a 3-7 antennomere club; body color testaceous, castaneous, or black (rarely bicolored), surface usually shining; elytral striae paired or approximately equally spaced; wings fully developed, folded, functional; mesosternal / metasternal process absent; metatibiae with 2 apical spurs, spurs set below and above the tarsal articulation (tarsus moves between tibial spurs); abdominal ventrites without a longitudinal ridge on each side; claws simple, without a tooth on the concave side; metatibiae with an interrupted or complete, obliquely transverse spinose ridge near the middle (sometimes absent).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3081DCA611BFFEEFF23FDCA76B1C4F1" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAD4E41611BFFEEFF23FDCA76B1C4F1" blockId="9.[192,1440,518,926]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B9669253611BFFEEFF23FDCA7575C571" bold="true" box="[192,325,518,542]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Remarks.</emphasis>
The tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611BFFEEFE21FDCA767CC571" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1855" box="[450,588,518,542]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Liparetrini">Liparetrini</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="F3050ED1611BFFEEFD1AFDCA775FC571" box="[761,879,518,542]" name="Australia" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Australia</collectingCountry>
and there is little merit to the previous placement New World taxa in this tribe by some authors (for a definition and detailed treatment of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611BFFEEFAF0FDEA71ACC551" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1855" box="[1299,1436,550,574]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Liparetrini">Liparetrini</taxonomicName>
, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8333B0611BFFEEFF0FFD8A75A1C531" author="Britton, E. B." box="[236,401,582,606]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 209" refId="ref17809" refString="Britton, E. B. 1980. A revision of the Australian chafers (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae) vol. 3 Tribe Liparetrini: Genus Liparetrus. Australian Journal of Zoology Supplementary Series 76: 1 - 209." type="book chapter" year="1980">Britton [1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8333B0611BFFEEFE7FFD8A75ECC531" author="Britton, E. B." box="[412,476,582,606]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="159 - 195" refId="ref17851" refString="Britton, E. B. 1990. A synopsis of the Australian genera of Liparetrini (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Invertebrate Taxonomy 4: 159 - 195." type="journal article" year="1990">1990</bibRefCitation>
]). Accordingly, the genera 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611BFFEEFCFAFD8A77A4C531" authorityName="Blanchard. The Neotropical" authorityYear="1850" box="[793,916,582,606]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Aplodema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9669253611BFFEEFCFAFD8A77A4C531" box="[793,916,582,606]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Aplodema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611BFFEEFC42FD8A707EC531" authorityName="Blanchard" authorityYear="1850" box="[929,1102,582,606]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Blepharotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9669253611BFFEEFC42FD8A707EC531" box="[929,1102,582,606]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Blepharotoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the New World species formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611BFFEEFE4EFDAB761AC511" authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1830" box="[429,554,615,638]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Heteronyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9669253611BFFEEFE4EFDAB761AC511" box="[429,554,615,638]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Heteronyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have all been transferred to the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611BFFEEFBEDFDAA70A4C511" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1847" box="[1038,1172,614,638]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Sericoidini">Sericoidini</taxonomicName>
(see above under the heading for 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611BFFEEFEACFD4A75CCC5F1" authorityName="Blanchard" authorityYear="1850" box="[335,508,646,670]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Blepharotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9669253611BFFEEFEACFD4A75CCC5F1" box="[335,508,646,670]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Blepharotoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8333B0611BFFEEFDF2FD4B7680C5F1" author="Evans, A. V." box="[529,688,646,670]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 458" refId="ref18146" refString="Evans, A. V. 2003. A checklist of the New World chafers (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Zootaxa 211: 1 - 458." type="journal article" year="2003">Evans (2003)</bibRefCitation>
also listed the monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611BFFEEFBD7FD4A70CCC5F1" authority="Saylor" authorityName="Saylor" authorityYear="1945" box="[1076,1276,646,670]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Zaburina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9669253611BFFEEFBD7FD4A7098C5F1" box="[1076,1192,646,670]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Zaburina</emphasis>
Saylor
</taxonomicName>
(from 
<collectingCountry id="F3050ED1611BFFEEFAAAFD4A74D7C5D1" name="Colombia" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Colombia</collectingCountry>
) and the species 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611BFFEEFE57FD6A773CC5D1" authority="(Saylor)" baseAuthorityName="Saylor" box="[436,780,678,702]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Aplodema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis id="B9669253611BFFEEFE57FD6A7696C5D1" box="[436,678,678,702]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Aplodema rufescens</emphasis>
(Saylor)
</taxonomicName>
(from 
<collectingCountry id="F3050ED1611BFFEEFCB9FD6A778CC5D1" box="[858,956,678,702]" name="Guyana" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Guyana</collectingCountry>
) in the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611BFFEEFBB4FD6A70D4C5D1" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1855" box="[1111,1252,678,702]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Liparetrini">Liparetrini</taxonomicName>
. These taxa are here removed from the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611BFFEEFDF4FD0A76AFC5B1" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1855" box="[535,671,710,734]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Liparetrini">Liparetrini</taxonomicName>
and placed in 
<emphasis id="B9669253611BFFEEFCA9FD0B77DDC5B1" box="[842,1005,710,734]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">incertae sedis</emphasis>
, pending a thorough examination of the type material. I will refrain from speculating on the proper classification of these taxa other than to say that their previous placement and possibly the distribution given are highly dubious. I examined the 
<typeStatus id="54A9F0E3611BFFEEFF23FCEA7517C451" box="[192,295,806,830]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611BFFEEFEABFCEA7693C451" authority="Saylor" authorityName="Saylor" box="[328,675,806,830]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Zaburina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="columbiana">
<emphasis id="B9669253611BFFEEFEABFCEA767FC451" box="[328,591,806,830]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Zaburina columbiana</emphasis>
Saylor
</taxonomicName>
a few years ago at the California Academy of Sciences and noted that it had a labrum projecting below clypeus, metatibial spurs on either side of tarsus, and propygidial suture evident. These characters suggest that this taxon might either belong in the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C2611BFFEEFB3DFCAA710CC411" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" box="[1246,1340,870,894]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Sericini">Sericini</taxonomicName>
or could be a mislabeled Australian specimen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
